The paper deals with graph theory and parameterized complexity, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem of finding a small vertex-separator is also related to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cuts in graphs, which is a topic in cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
